good reference of roofit tutorails:

1.import tree data and apply cuts : 
https://root.cern.ch/doc/v608/rf401__importttreethx_8C.html 
https://root.cern.ch/doc/v608/rf402__datahandling_8C.html


2.fitresult save and read :
https://root.cern.ch/doc/v608/rf607__fitresult_8C.html
https://root.cern.ch/doc/v608/rf608__fitresultaspdf_8C.html

3.MC study
https://root.cern.ch/doc/v608/rf801__mcstudy_8C.html
http://roofit.sourceforge.net/docs/tutorial/fitgen/roofit_tutorial_fitgen.pdf
an simeple example code from Camelia is in the subfolder


4. about chebyshev : roofit use chebyshev irst kind : http://mathworld.wolfram.com/ChebyshevPolynomialoftheFirstKind.html
= 1+ sum(1,n)AiTi, so a 3rd order chebyshev would only have three parameter in roofit (just like simple polynimial, no zero order term parameter)
root default has chebyshev function , can be called by like :
TF1 * f = (TF1*) gROOT->GetFunction("chebyshev4");



